run:
aclocal
autoconf
automake -a 
./configure --prefix `pwd`
make
make install

files will be in ./bin

To compile, create a file in src/include called defaultAddresses.h, substituting 
the IP addresses with yours and another host's (or yours again for local 
testing). See example below:

/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/ 

#ifndef _DEFAULT_ADDRESSES_H_
#define _DEFAULT_ADDRESSES_H_

#define MY_ADDRESS  "192.168.1.183"
#define THEIR_ADDRESS "192.168.1.164"

#endif

/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/ 
